      "content": {
        "title": "Glycolysis Pathway Overview",
        "definition": "Ten-step cytoplasmic pathway converting one glucose molecule to two pyruvate molecules with net production of ATP and NADH.",
        "summary": "Glycolysis is the universal first stage of glucose catabolism. It proceeds without oxygen and provides ATP and biosynthetic precursors."
      },
