      "resolution_level": 4,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_chemistry_l3_glycolysis_and_central_metabolism",
      "content": {
        "title": "Glycolysis Regulatory Steps",
        "definition": "Allosteric and hormonal control of irreversible glycolytic enzymes hexokinase, phosphofructokinase-1, and pyruvate kinase to match flux to cellular energy demand.",
        "summary": "PFK-1 is the primary flux-control step, inhibited by ATP and citrate and activated by AMP. Insulin and glucagon modulate glycolysis through kinase/phosphatase cascades."
      },
