      "content": {
        "title": "Net ATP Yield from Glycolysis",
        "definition": "Accounting of two ATP invested and four ATP produced per glucose, yielding net two ATP and two NADH molecules per glucose molecule oxidized to pyruvate.",
        "summary": "Per-glucose stoichiometry: 2 ATP consumed, 4 ATP produced, net +2 ATP. Each NADH can yield additional ATP if shuttled into oxidative phosphorylation."
